*ibm2_rm* branch is running on RHEL 9.2 with the pam version : 1.5.1-15.el9_2.x86_64. There was a bug reported in previous RHEL version : https://www.findbugzero.com/operational-defect-database/vendors/rh/defects/RHEL-20943

and the fix of it got introduced in : https://rpm.pbone.net/changelog_idpl_90101502_com_pam-1.5.1-19.el9.i686.rpm.html#:~:text=*%20Mon%20Jan%2008%202024%20Iker%20Pedrosa%20%2D%201.5.1%2D17%2D%20pam_faillock%3A%20create%20tallydir%20before%20creating%20tallyfile.%20Resolves%3A%20RHEL%2D20943

The platform_team branch is running on rhel9.4 which have the fix of it. 

 !image-2025-06-23-15-40-09-159.png|thumbnail! ;;;

column1: DODIN APL : RHEL9 : AuditServiceInactive alert is not raising when auditd is inactive
column30:
steps to reproduce:
1. Login the dodin cluster.
2. Verify the auditd service is running in all the nodes.
{code}
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$ allssh.sh 'printf "Cohe\$1tyCohe\$1ty" | sudo -S systemctl is-active auditd' | grep "active"
[sudo] password for support: active
[sudo] password for support: active
[sudo] password for support: active
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$
{code}
3. Stop the auditd service in any one node and verify that.
{code}
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$ printf "Cohe\$1tyCohe\$1ty" | sudo -S service auditd stop
[sudo] password for support: Stopping logging: 
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$ printf "Cohe\$1tyCohe\$1ty" | sudo -S systemctl is-active auditd
inactive
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$
{code}
4. Wait for few min and check the alerts
{code}
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$ iris_cli --username='admin' --password='admin' --skip_force_password_change=true --skip_password_prompt=true alert list states=kOpen | grep -A9 "ALERT.*CODE.*:.*CE00401153"
[support@ve-kms-cluster-005056af1e24-node-1 ~]$
{code}

Expected : AuditServiceInactive alert should be raised

Actual: No alert raised. 
Ref:  !Screenshot from 2025-06-20 22-09-43.png|thumbnail!  !Screenshot from 2025-06-20 22-11-55.png|thumbnail!

column1: Dodin : Rhel9 : Audit rules does not shows up login rule (-w /var/log/faillock -p wa -k logins)
column30:
As per the https://jira.cohesity.com/browse/ENG-472857, followed below steps,

1. enable the gflags - iris_cli cluster update-gflag service-name=nexus gflag-name=enable_auditd_service gflag-value=true reason=enable_audit
{code}
[support@c2605-haswell-bqkp91500079-node-1 ~]$ iris_cli cluster update-gflag service-name=nexus gflag-name=enable_auditd_service gflag-value=true reason=enable_audit
 Username: admin
 'admin' Password: 
Success: All Gflags updated successfully.
NOTE: Updated Gflag name: enable_auditd_service, value: true will be effective only after "nexus" service restart.
SERVICE NAME                  : nexus

GFLAG                         : enable_auditd_service, true
REASON                        : enable_audit
TIMESTAMP                     : Wednesday, 11-Jun-25 15:08:22 UTC


[support@c2605-haswell-bqkp91500079-node-1 ~]$
{code}
2. Restart the nexus service.
{code}
[support@c2605-haswell-bqkp91500079-node-1 ~]$ nexus.sh stop; nexus.sh start
sudo systemctl stop nexus.service
[sudo] password for support: 
sudo systemctl start nexus.service
1666984
[support@c2605-haswell-bqkp91500079-node-1 ~]$ ssh 10.2.195.149
*****************  Welcome to Cohesity ******************

WARNING: Unauthorized access to this system is forbidden.
By accessing this system, you agree that your actions
may be monitored if unauthorized usage is suspected.

*********************************************************

11/Jun/25 2:09 AM;satvik.arora;synced with [~muthukaruppan.palpandi] regarding this today morning. we ran the cleanup script, yet some v1 alerts were not cleaned up.

RCA:
93 alerts in "alert" index do not have an corresponding helios account id, while deletion we check for account id and cluster id both, so these alerts were not deleted.
v1 api gets alerts based on clusters thus these alerts were showing up in the response.

Next Steps:
will get [~bambam.shivam]'s opinion on if this looks like an one off event or it is possible in future as well
1. if one off will just delete these alerts from the index
2. if this can happen in future, will remove check for account id in automationserver for alerts deletion and delete all alerts for a cluster in "alert" ES index for the given time range.

cc:[~julian.simon]
